    "Warren W. Wiersbe": "Paul closed this memorable occasion by kneeling down and praying for his friends, and then they all wept together. It is a difficult thing to say good-bye, especially when you know you will not see your friends again in this life. But we have the blessed assurance that we will one day see our Christian friends and loved ones in heaven when Jesus Christ returns (1 Thess. 4:13 [c_1Th_4] [v_1Th_4_13] \u201318). Meanwhile, there is a job to be done\u2014so, let\u2019s do it! QUESTIONS FOR PERSONAL REFLECTION OR GROUP DISCUSSION",
